column5: I drove up the Selwyn Rd. yesterday Jer and noticed Chemong is pretty well frozen right across although there's still open spots around.  Clear is wide open except for some ice along the shore.  Gettin to be that time of year.
No snow since last week here...sucks to be in the snowbelt don't it?
Highs of 77 -79 for the next week, lows around 50.  No snow in the drive but there is ice in the fridge...
OK..LOL  all this snow will not help simcoe and cooks bay freeze........
